This paper presents a novel algorithm for detecting sample corruption in a training dataset, which is a common problem in machine learning. The algorithm is applicable to any supervised machine learning task and involves optimizing the performance of the network on a clean validation set using gradient descent. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, given the focus on machine learning and optimization, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
